titles.title: To direct the Secretary of the Interior to transfer to John R. and Margaret J. Lowe of Big Horn County, Wyoming, certain land so as to correct an error in the patent issued to their predecessors in interest.

action.text: Referred to the House Committee on Resources.
Referred to the Subcommittee on National Parks and Public Lands.
Subcommittee Consideration and Mark-up Session Held.
Forwarded by Subcommittee to Full Committee by Voice Vote.
Committee Consideration and Mark-up Session Held.

calendar.text: Ordered to be Reported by Voice Vote.

action.text: Reported by the Committee on Resources. H. Rept. 106-68.

calendar.text: Placed on the Private Calendar, Calendar No. 2.

action.text: Called up from the Private Calendar for consideration.

vote.text: On passage Passed by voice vote.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

calendar.text: Received in the Senate. Read twice. Placed on Senate Legislative Calendar under General Orders. Calendar No. 105.

action.text: Indefinitely postponed by Senate by Unanimous Consent.

bill.summary: 2/2/1999--Introduced. Directs the Secretary of the Interior to transfer certain property in Big Horn County, Wyoming, to two named individuals.
